Cold Noodle Salad with Peanut Dressing
  --Hetty Lui McKinnon

Dressing:
1/2 c smooth peanut butter (not natural)
1/4 c shoyu
2 tbsp maple syrup
2 tbsp lime juice (from 1 lime)
1 tbsp sesame oil
2 tsp chile oil or hot sauce + more to taste
1 garlic clove, grated

In a medium bowl, combine the peanut butter, shoyu, maple syrup, lime juice, sesame oil, chile oil or hot sauce, and garlic. Add 1/4 - 1/2 c water, 1 tbsp at a time, and whisk until the sauce is a pourable consistency. Taste and add more chile oil or hot sauce as desired; set aside.

Salad:
Kosher salt
10 oz soba noodles
1 medium zucchini or cucumber (~6 oz)
5 radishes (~4 oz)
1 bell pepper (any color)
1 tbsp sesame oil
1/2 c roasted salted peanuts (~2 oz), roughly chopped
2 scallions, trimmed and finely chopped
handful of cilantro leaves
1 lime, cut into wedges for serving

Bring a pot of salted water to the boil. Add the soba, stir to prevent sticking, and cook according to package instructions until just tender. Rinse under cold water until the noodles are completely cold. Cut the zucchini or cucumber and radishes into 1/8" thick slices, then cut into thin matchsticks. Slice the peppers into 1/8" pieces. Place them all in a large bowl. Loosen the soba noodles by running them under some water, then allow to drain again. Add the soba noodles to the vegetables, add the remaining 1 tbsp sesame oil and toss to combine. When you are ready to serve, drizzle with spicy peanut sauce and top with peanuts, scallions and cilantro. Serve immediately, with lime wedges alongside. 


Notes: can add fresh grated ginger to the dressing

